7545 nd=toNamespaceDefMutable(buildScopeFromQualifiedName(root->name.left(i+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo()));
7546 }
7547 }
7548 else // no scope, check the scope in which the docs where found
7549 {
7550 if (root->parent()->section.isScope() && !root->parent()->name.isEmpty()) // found enum docs inside a compound
7551 {
7552 scope=root->parent()->name;
7553 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr) nd=getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scope);
7554 }
7555 name=root->name;
7556 }
7557
7558 if (!root->relates.isEmpty())
7559 { // related member, prefix user specified scope
7560 isRelated=TRUE;
7561 if (getClassMutable(root->relates)==nullptr && !scope.isEmpty())
7562 scope=mergeScopes(scope,root->relates);
7563 else
7564 scope=root->relates;
7565 if ((cd=getClassMutable(scope))==nullptr) nd=getResolvedNamespaceMutable(scope);
7566 }
7567
7568 if (cd && !name.isEmpty()) // found a enum inside a compound
7569 {
7570 //printf("Enum in class '%s'::'%s'\n",qPrint(cd->name()),qPrint(name));
7571 fd=nullptr;
7572 mnsd=Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap;
7573 isGlobal=false;
7574 }
7575 else if (nd && !nd->isAnonymous()) // found enum inside namespace
7576 {
7577 //printf("Enum in namespace '%s'::'%s'\n",qPrint(nd->name()),qPrint(name));
7578 mnsd=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap;
7579 isGlobal=true;
7580 }
7581 else // found a global enum
7582 {
7583 fd=root->fileDef();

7585 mnsd=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap;
7586 isGlobal=true;
7587 }
7588

7596 {

7598 name(n), member(std::move(md)) {}
7599 QCString name;
7600 std::unique_ptr<MemberDef> member;
7601 };

7605 {
7606 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
7607 // use raw pointer in this loop, since we modify mn and can then invalidate mdp.
7608 if (md && md->isEnumerate() && !root->children().empty())
7609 {
7610 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("enum {} with {} children",md->name(),root->children().size());

7613 SrcLangExt sle = root->lang;
7614 bool isJavaLike = sle==SrcLangExt::CSharp || sle==SrcLangExt::Java || sle==SrcLangExt::XML;
7615 if ( isJavaLike || root->spec.isStrong())
7616 {
7617 // Unlike classic C/C++ enums, for C++11, C# & Java enum
7618 // values are only visible inside the enum scope, so we must create
7619 // them here and only add them to the enum

7621 // qPrint(md->qualifiedName()),qPrint(e->name),(void*)e->tagInfo(),qPrint(e->name));

7623 if (isJavaLike)

7626 }

7630 if (fileName.isEmpty() && e->tagInfo())
7631 {
7632 fileName = e->tagInfo()->tagName;
7633 }

7636 fileName,e->startLine,e->startColumn,
7637 e->type,e->name,e->args,QCString(),
7638 e->protection, Specifier::Normal,e->isStatic,Relationship::Member,
7639 MemberType::EnumValue,ArgumentList(),ArgumentList(),e->metaData);
7640 auto fmmd = toMemberDefMutable(fmd.get());
7641 NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
7642 if (md->getClassDef())
7643 fmmd->setMemberClass(md->getClassDef());
7644 else if (mnd && (mnd->isLinkable() || mnd->isAnonymous()))
7645 fmmd->setNamespace(mnd);
7646 else if (md->getFileDef())
7647 fmmd->setFileDef(md->getFileDef());
7648 fmmd->setOuterScope(md->getOuterScope());
7649 fmmd->setTagInfo(e->tagInfo());
7650 fmmd->setLanguage(e->lang);
7651 fmmd->setBodySegment(e->startLine,e->bodyLine,e->endBodyLine);
7652 fmmd->setBodyDef(e->fileDef());
7653 fmmd->setId(e->id);
7654 fmmd->setDocumentation(e->doc,e->docFile,e->docLine);
7655 fmmd->setBriefDescription(e->brief,e->briefFile,e->briefLine);
7656 fmmd->addSectionsToDefinition(e->anchors);
7657 std::string init = e->initializer.str();
7658 fmmd->setInitializer(init.c_str());
7659 fmmd->setMaxInitLines(e->initLines);
7660 fmmd->setMemberGroupId(e->mGrpId);
7661 fmmd->setExplicitExternal(e->explicitExternal,fileName,e->startLine,e->startColumn);
7662 fmmd->setRefItems(e->sli);
7663 fmmd->setAnchor();
7664 md->insertEnumField(fmd.get());
7665 fmmd->setEnumScope(md,TRUE);
7666 extraMembers.emplace_back(e->name,std::move(fmd));
7667 }
7668 }
7669 else
7670 {
7671 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("enum value {}",e->name);
7672 //printf("e->name=%s isRelated=%d\n",qPrint(e->name),isRelated);
7673 MemberName *fmn=nullptr;
7674 MemberNameLinkedMap *emnsd = isRelated ? Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap : mnsd;
7675 if (!e->name.isEmpty() && (fmn=emnsd->find(e->name)))
7676 // get list of members with the same name as the field
7677 {
7678 for (const auto &ifmd : *fmn)
7679 {
7680 MemberDefMutable *fmd = toMemberDefMutable(ifmd.get());
7681 if (fmd && fmd->isEnumValue() && fmd->getOuterScope()==md->getOuterScope()) // in same scope
7682 {
7683 //printf("found enum value with same name %s in scope %s\n",
7684 // qPrint(fmd->name()),qPrint(fmd->getOuterScope()->name()));
7685 if (nd && !nd->isAnonymous())
7686 {
7687 if (!fmd->isStrongEnumValue()) // only non strong enum values can be globally added
7688 {
7689 const NamespaceDef *fnd=fmd->getNamespaceDef();
7690 if (fnd==nd) // enum value is inside a namespace
7691 {
7692 md->insertEnumField(fmd);
7693 fmd->setEnumScope(md);
7694 }
7695 }
7696 }
7697 else if (isGlobal)
7698 {
7699 if (!fmd->isStrongEnumValue()) // only non strong enum values can be globally added
7700 {
7701 const FileDef *ffd=fmd->getFileDef();
7702 if (ffd==fd && ffd==md->getFileDef()) // enum value has file scope
7703 {
7704 md->insertEnumField(fmd);
7705 fmd->setEnumScope(md);
7706 }
7707 }
7708 }
7709 else if (isRelated && cd) // reparent enum value to
7710 // match the enum's scope
7711 {
7712 md->insertEnumField(fmd); // add field def to list
7713 fmd->setEnumScope(md); // cross ref with enum name
7714 fmd->setEnumClassScope(cd); // cross ref with enum name
7715 fmd->setOuterScope(cd);
7716 fmd->makeRelated();
7717 cd->insertMember(fmd);
7718 }
7719 else
7720 {
7721 if (!fmd->isStrongEnumValue()) // only non strong enum values can be globally added
7722 {
7723 const ClassDef *fcd=fmd->getClassDef();
7724 if (fcd==cd) // enum value is inside a class
7725 {
7726 //printf("Inserting enum field %s in enum scope %s\n",
7727 // qPrint(fmd->name()),qPrint(md->name()));

7729 fmd->setEnumScope(md); // cross ref with enum name
7730 }
7731 }
7732 }
7733 }
7734 }
7735 }
7736 }
7737 }
7738 }
7739 }
7740 // move the newly added members into mn
7741 for (auto &e : extraMembers)
7742 {
7743 MemberName *emn=mnsd->add(e.name);
7744 emn->push_back(std::move(e.member));
7745 }
7746 }
7747 }
7748 }
7749 else
7750 {
7751 for (const auto &e : root->children()) addEnumValuesToEnums(e.get());
7752 }

11813 err("Failed to map file extension '%s' to unsupported language '%s'.\n"
11814 "Check the EXTENSION_MAPPING setting in the config file.\n",
11815 qPrint(ext),qPrint(language));
11816 }
11817 else
11818 {
11819 msg("Adding custom extension mapping: '%s' will be treated as language '%s'\n",
11820 qPrint(ext),qPrint(language));
11821 }
11822 }
11823 }
11824 // create input file exncodings
11825
11826 // check INPUT_ENCODING
11827 void *cd = portable_iconv_open("UTF-8",Config_getString(INPUT_ENCODING).data());
11828 if (cd==reinterpret_cast<void *>(-1))
11829 {
11830 term("unsupported character conversion: '%s'->'%s': %s\n"
11831 "Check the 'INPUT_ENCODING' setting in the config file!\n",
11832 qPrint(Config_getString(INPUT_ENCODING)),qPrint("UTF-8"),strerror(errno));
11833 }
11834 else
11835 {
11836 portable_iconv_close(cd);
11837 }
11838
11839 // check and split INPUT_FILE_ENCODING
11840 const StringVector &fileEncod = Config_getList(INPUT_FILE_ENCODING);
11841 for (const auto &mapping : fileEncod)
11842 {
11843 QCString mapStr = mapping.c_str();
11844 int i=mapStr.find('=');
11845 if (i==-1)
11846 {
11847 continue;
11848 }
11849 else
11850 {
11851 QCString pattern = mapStr.left(i).stripWhiteSpace().lower();
11852 QCString encoding = mapStr.mid(i+1).stripWhiteSpace().lower();
11853 if (pattern.isEmpty() || encoding.isEmpty())
11854 {
11855 continue;
11856 }
11857 cd = portable_iconv_open("UTF-8",encoding.data());
11858 if (cd==reinterpret_cast<void *>(-1))
11859 {
11860 term("unsupported character conversion: '%s'->'%s': %s\n"
11861 "Check the 'INPUT_FILE_ENCODING' setting in the config file!\n",
11862 qPrint(encoding),qPrint("UTF-8"),strerror(errno));
11863 }
11864 else
11865 {
11866 portable_iconv_close(cd);
11867 }
11868
11869 Doxygen::inputFileEncodingList.emplace_back(pattern, encoding);
11870 }
11871 }
11872
11873 // add predefined macro name to a dictionary
11874 const StringVector &expandAsDefinedList =Config_getList(EXPAND_AS_DEFINED);
11875 for (const auto &s : expandAsDefinedList)
11876 {
11877 Doxygen::expandAsDefinedSet.insert(s.c_str());
11878 }
11879
11880 // read aliases and store them in a dictionary
11881 readAliases();
11882
11883 // store number of spaces in a tab into Doxygen::spaces
11884 int tabSize = Config_getInt(TAB_SIZE);
11885 Doxygen::spaces.resize(tabSize);
11886 for (int sp=0; sp<tabSize; sp++) Doxygen::spaces.at(sp)=' ';
11887 Doxygen::spaces.at(tabSize)='\0';

◆ findEndOfTemplate()

static int findEndOfTemplate ( const QCString & s,
size_t startPos )
static

Searches for the end of a template in prototype s starting from character position startPos. If the end was found the position of the closing > is returned, otherwise -1 is returned.

Handles exotic cases such as

Class<(id<0)>
Class<bits<<2>
Class<"<">
Class<'<'>
Class<(")<")>
MemberListContainer::Class
@ Class

Definition at line 4627 of file doxygen.cpp.

4628{
4629 // locate end of template
4630 size_t e=startPos;
4631 int brCount=1;
4632 int roundCount=0;
4633 size_t len = s.length();
4634 bool insideString=FALSE;
4635 bool insideChar=FALSE;
4636 char pc = 0;
4637 while (e<len && brCount!=0)
4638 {
4639 char c=s.at(e);
4640 switch(c)
4641 {
4642 case '<':
4643 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4644 {
4645 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='<')
4646 e++;
4647 else if (roundCount==0)
4648 brCount++;
4649 }
4650 break;
4651 case '>':
4652 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4653 {
4654 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='>')
4655 e++;
4656 else if (roundCount==0)
4657 brCount--;
4658 }
4659 break;
4660 case '(':
4661 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4662 roundCount++;
4663 break;
4664 case ')':
4665 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4666 roundCount--;
4667 break;
4668 case '"':
4669 if (!insideChar)
4670 {
4671 if (insideString && pc!='\\')
4672 insideString=FALSE;
4673 else
4674 insideString=TRUE;
4675 }
4676 break;
4677 case '\'':
4678 if (!insideString)
4679 {
4680 if (insideChar && pc!='\\')
4681 insideChar=FALSE;
4682 else
4683 insideChar=TRUE;
4684 }
4685 break;
4686 }
4687 pc = c;
4688 e++;
4689 }
4690 return brCount==0 ? static_cast<int>(e) : -1;

The boolean overloaded is used to specify whether or not a standard overload documentation line should be generated.

The boolean isFunc is a hint that indicates that this is a function instead of a variable or typedef.

6731 {

6739 }

6741 else
6742 {
6743 if (isFunc) // a function => we use argList for the arguments
6744 {

6746 }
6747 else // variable => add 'argument' list

6750 }
6751 }
6752 }

6754 {

6760 }

6764 }
6765 }

6770 funcDecl=funcName+funcTempList;
6771 }
6772 else

6774 funcDecl=funcName+funcArgs;
6775 }
6776 }

6784 " exceptions='{}' isRelated={} isMemberOf={} isFriend={} isFunc={}",

2916 {
2917 result=FALSE; // arg type is a known type
2918 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("known type: result={}",result);
2919 return result;
2920 }
2921 if (checkIfTypedef(ctx,fd,a.type))
2922 {
2923 result=FALSE; // argument is a typedef
2924 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("typedef: result={}",result);
2925 return result;
2926 }
2927 std::string atype = a.type.str();
2928 if (reg::search(atype,match,initChars) && match.position()==0)
2929 {
2930 result=TRUE; // argument type starts with typical initializer char
2931 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("argument with init char: result={}",result);
2932 return result;
2933 }
2934 std::string resType=resolveTypeDef(ctx,a.type).str();
2935 if (resType.empty()) resType=atype;
2936 static const reg::Ex idChars(R"(\a\w*)");
2937 if (reg::search(resType,match,idChars) && match.position()==0) // resType starts with identifier
2938 {
2939 resType=match.str();
2940 if (resType=="int" || resType=="long" ||
2941 resType=="float" || resType=="double" ||
2942 resType=="char" || resType=="void" ||
2943 resType=="signed" || resType=="unsigned" ||
2944 resType=="const" || resType=="volatile" )
2945 {
2946 result=FALSE; // type keyword -> function prototype
2947 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("type keyword: result={}",result);
2948 return result;
2949 }
2950 }
2951 }
2952 result=TRUE;
2953 }
2954
2955 AUTO_TRACE_EXIT("end: result={}",result);
2956 return result;
2957}
2958
2959static void addVariable(const Entry *root,int isFuncPtr=-1)
2960{
2961 bool sliceOpt = Config_getBool(OPTIMIZE_OUTPUT_SLICE);
2962
2963 AUTO_TRACE("VARIABLE_SEC: type='{}' name='{}' args='{}' bodyLine={} endBodyLine={} mGrpId={} relates='{}'",
2964 root->type, root->name, root->args, root->bodyLine, root->endBodyLine, root->mGrpId, root->relates);
2965 //printf("root->parent->name=%s\n",qPrint(root->parent->name));
2966
2967 QCString type = root->type;
2968 QCString name = root->name;
2969 QCString args = root->args;
2970 if (type.isEmpty() && name.find("operator")==-1 &&
2971 (name.find('*')!=-1 || name.find('&')!=-1))
2972 {
2973 // recover from parse error caused by redundant braces
2974 // like in "int *(var[10]);", which is parsed as
2975 // type="" name="int *" args="(var[10])"
2976
2977 type=name;
2978 std::string sargs = args.str();
2979 static const reg::Ex reName(R"(\a\w*)");
2980 reg::Match match;
2981 if (reg::search(sargs,match,reName))
2982 {
2983 name = match.str(); // e.g. 'var' in '(var[10])'
2984 sargs = match.suffix().str(); // e.g. '[10]) in '(var[10])'
2985 size_t j = sargs.find(')');
2986 if (j!=std::string::npos) args=sargs.substr(0,j); // extract, e.g '[10]' from '[10])'
2987 }
2988 }
2989 else
2990 {
2991 int i=isFuncPtr;
2992 if (i==-1 && (root->spec.isAlias())==0) i=findFunctionPtr(type.str(),root->lang); // for typedefs isFuncPtr is not yet set
2993 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("functionPtr={}",i!=-1?"yes":"no");
2994 if (i>=0) // function pointer
2995 {
2996 int ai = type.find('[',i);
2997 if (ai>i) // function pointer array
2998 {
2999 args.prepend(type.right(type.length()-ai));
3000 type=type.left(ai);
3001 }
3002 else if (type.find(')',i)!=-1) // function ptr, not variable like "int (*bla)[10]"
3003 {
3004 type=type.left(type.length()-1);
3005 args.prepend(") ");
3006 }
3007 }
3008 }
3009 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("after correction: type='{}' name='{}' args='{}'",type,name,args);
3010
3011 QCString scope;
3012 name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(name);
3013
3014 // find the scope of this variable
3015 int index = computeQualifiedIndex(name);
3016 if (index!=-1 && root->parent()->section.isGroupDoc() && root->parent()->tagInfo())
3017 // grouped members are stored with full scope
3018 {
3019 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(name.left(index+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo());
3020 scope=name.left(index);
3021 name=name.mid(index+2);
3022 }
3023 else
3024 {
3025 Entry *p = root->parent();
3026 while (p->section.isScope())
3027 {
3028 QCString scopeName = p->name;
3029 if (!scopeName.isEmpty())
3030 {
3031 scope.prepend(scopeName);
3032 break;
3033 }
3034 p=p->parent();
3035 }
3036 }
3037
3038 type=type.stripWhiteSpace();
3039 ClassDefMutable *cd=nullptr;
3040 bool isRelated=FALSE;
3041 bool isMemberOf=FALSE;
3042
3043 QCString classScope=stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(scope);
3044 classScope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(classScope,FALSE);
3045 QCString annScopePrefix=scope.left(scope.length()-classScope.length());
3046
3047 if (name.findRev("::")!=-1)
3048 {
3049 if (type=="friend class" || type=="friend struct" ||
3050 type=="friend union")
3051 {
3052 cd=getClassMutable(scope);
3053 if (cd)
3054 {
3055 addVariableToClass(root, // entry
3056 cd, // class to add member to
3057 MemberType::Friend, // type of member
3058 type, // type value as string
3059 name, // name of the member
3060 args, // arguments as string
3061 FALSE, // from Anonymous scope
3062 nullptr, // anonymous member
3063 Protection::Public, // protection
3064 Relationship::Member // related to a class
3065 );
3066 }
3067 }
3068 if (root->bodyLine!=-1 && root->endBodyLine!=-1) // store the body location for later use
3069 {
3070 Doxygen::staticInitMap.emplace(name.str(),BodyInfo{root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine});
3071 }
3072
3073
3074 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("static variable {} body=[{}..{}]",name,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3075 return; /* skip this member, because it is a
3076 * static variable definition (always?), which will be
3077 * found in a class scope as well, but then we know the
3078 * correct protection level, so only then it will be
3079 * inserted in the correct list!
3080 */
3081 }
3082
3083 MemberType mtype = MemberType::Variable;
3084 if (type=="@")
3085 mtype=MemberType::EnumValue;
3086 else if (type.startsWith("typedef "))
3087 mtype=MemberType::Typedef;
3088 else if (type.startsWith("friend "))
3089 mtype=MemberType::Friend;
3090 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Property)
3091 mtype=MemberType::Property;
3092 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Event)
3093 mtype=MemberType::Event;
3094 else if (type.find("sequence<") != -1)
3095 mtype=sliceOpt ? MemberType::Sequence : MemberType::Typedef;
3096 else if (type.find("dictionary<") != -1)
3097 mtype=sliceOpt ? MemberType::Dictionary : MemberType::Typedef;
3098
3099 if (!root->relates.isEmpty()) // related variable
3100 {
3101 isRelated=TRUE;
3102 isMemberOf=(root->relatesType==RelatesType::MemberOf);
3103 if (getClass(root->relates)==nullptr && !scope.isEmpty())
3104 scope=mergeScopes(scope,root->relates);
3105 else
3106 scope=root->relates;
3107 }
3108
3109 cd=getClassMutable(scope);
3110 if (cd==nullptr && classScope!=scope) cd=getClassMutable(classScope);
3111 if (cd)
3112 {
3113 MemberDef *md=nullptr;
3114
3115 // if cd is an anonymous (=tag less) scope we insert the member
3116 // into a non-anonymous parent scope as well. This is needed to
3117 // be able to refer to it using \var or \fn
3118
3119 //int indentDepth=0;
3120 int si=scope.find('@');
3121 //int anonyScopes = 0;
3122 //bool added=FALSE;
3123
3124 bool inlineSimpleStructs = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
3125 Relationship relationship = isMemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign :
3126 isRelated ? Relationship::Related :
3127 Relationship::Member ;
3128 if (si!=-1 && !inlineSimpleStructs) // anonymous scope or type
3129 {
3130 QCString pScope;
3131 ClassDefMutable *pcd=nullptr;
3132 pScope = scope.left(std::max(si-2,0)); // scope without tag less parts
3133 if (!pScope.isEmpty())
3134 pScope.prepend(annScopePrefix);
3135 else if (annScopePrefix.length()>2)
3136 pScope=annScopePrefix.left(annScopePrefix.length()-2);
3137 if (name.at(0)!='@')
3138 {
3139 if (!pScope.isEmpty() && (pcd=getClassMutable(pScope)))
3140 {
3141 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Adding anonymous member to scope '{}'",pScope);
3142 md=addVariableToClass(root, // entry
3143 pcd, // class to add member to
3144 mtype, // member type
3145 type, // type value as string
3146 name, // member name
3147 args, // arguments as string
3148 TRUE, // from anonymous scope
3149 nullptr, // from anonymous member
3150 root->protection,
3151 relationship
3152 );
3153 //added=TRUE;
3154 }
3155 else // anonymous scope inside namespace or file => put variable in the global scope
3156 {
3157 if (mtype==MemberType::Variable)
3158 {
3159 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Adding anonymous member to global scope '{}'");
3160 md=addVariableToFile(root,mtype,pScope,type,name,args,TRUE,nullptr);
3161 }
3162 //added=TRUE;
3163 }
3164 }
3165 }
3166
3167 addVariableToClass(root, // entry
3168 cd, // class to add member to
3169 mtype, // member type
3170 type, // type value as string
3171 name, // name of the member
3172 args, // arguments as string
3173 FALSE, // from anonymous scope
3174 md, // from anonymous member
3175 root->protection,
3176 relationship
3177 );
3178 }
3179 else if (!name.isEmpty()) // global variable
3180 {
3181 addVariableToFile(root,mtype,scope,type,name,args,FALSE,/*nullptr,*/nullptr);
3182 }
3183
3184}
3185
3186//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3187// Searches the Entry tree for typedef documentation sections.
3188// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3189static void buildTypedefList(const Entry *root)
3190{
3191 //printf("buildVarList(%s)\n",qPrint(rootNav->name()));
3192 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
3193 root->section.isVariable() &&
3194 root->type.find("typedef ")!=-1 // its a typedef
3195 )
3196 {
3197 AUTO_TRACE();
3198 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3199 QCString scope;
3200 int index = computeQualifiedIndex(rname);
3201 if (index!=-1 && root->parent()->section.isGroupDoc() && root->parent()->tagInfo())
3202 // grouped members are stored with full scope
3203 {
3204 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(rname.left(index+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo());
3205 scope=rname.left(index);
3206 rname=rname.mid(index+2);
3207 }
3208 else
3209 {
3210 scope=root->parent()->name; //stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->parent->name);
3211 }
3212 ClassDefMutable *cd=getClassMutable(scope);
3213 NamespaceDef *nd=getResolvedNamespace(scope);
3214 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(rname);
3215 bool found=false;
3216 if (mn) // symbol with the same name already found
3217 {
3218 for (auto &imd : *mn)
3219 {
3220 if (!imd->isTypedef())
3221 continue;
3222
3223 QCString rtype = root->type;
3224 rtype.stripPrefix("typedef ");
3225
3226 // merge the typedefs only if they're not both grouped, and both are
3227 // either part of the same class, part of the same namespace, or both
3228 // are global (i.e., neither in a class or a namespace)
3229 bool notBothGrouped = root->groups.empty() || imd->getGroupDef()==nullptr; // see example #100
3230 bool bothSameScope = (!cd && !nd) || (cd && imd->getClassDef() == cd) || (nd && imd->getNamespaceDef() == nd);
3231 //printf("imd->isTypedef()=%d imd->typeString()=%s root->type=%s\n",imd->isTypedef(),
3232 // qPrint(imd->typeString()),qPrint(root->type));
3233 if (notBothGrouped && bothSameScope && imd->typeString()==rtype)
3234 {
3235 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
3236 if (md)
3237 {
3238 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3239 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3240 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3241 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3242 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3243 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3244 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3245
3246 // merge ingroup specifiers
3247 if (md->getGroupDef()==nullptr && !root->groups.empty())
3248 {
3249 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3250 }
3251 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=nullptr && root->groups.empty())
3252 {
3253 //printf("existing member is grouped, new member not\n");
3254 }
3255 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=nullptr && !root->groups.empty())
3256 {
3257 //printf("both members are grouped\n");
3258 }
3259 found=true;
3260 break;
3261 }
3262 }
3263 }
3264 }
3265 if (found)
3266 {
3267 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("typedef '{}' already found",rname);
3268 // mark the entry as processed, as we copied everything from it elsewhere
3269 // also, otherwise, due to containing `typedef` it may later get treated
3270 // as a function typedef in filterMemberDocumentation, which is incorrect
3271 root->markAsProcessed();
3272 }
3273 else
3274 {
3275 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("new typedef '{}'",rname);
3276 addVariable(root);
3277 }
3278
3279 }
3280 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3281 if (!e->section.isEnum())
3282 buildTypedefList(e.get());
3283}

3285//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3286// Searches the Entry tree for sequence documentation sections.
3287// If found they are stored in the global list.
3288static void buildSequenceList(const Entry *root)
3289{
3290 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
3291 root->section.isVariable() &&
3292 root->type.find("sequence<")!=-1 // it's a sequence
3293 )
3294 {
3295 AUTO_TRACE();
3296 addVariable(root);
3297 }
3298 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3299 if (!e->section.isEnum())
3300 buildSequenceList(e.get());
3301}

3309 root->section.isVariable() &&
3310 root->type.find("dictionary<")!=-1 // it's a dictionary
3311 )
3312 {
3313 AUTO_TRACE();
3314 addVariable(root);

3318 buildDictionaryList(e.get());
3319}

3321//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3322// Searches the Entry tree for Variable documentation sections.
3323// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3324
3325static void buildVarList(const Entry *root)
3326{
3327 //printf("buildVarList(%s) section=%08x\n",qPrint(rootNav->name()),rootNav->section());
3328 int isFuncPtr=-1;
3329 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
3330 (root->type.isEmpty() || g_compoundKeywords.find(root->type.str())==g_compoundKeywords.end()) &&
3331 (
3332 (root->section.isVariable() && // it's a variable
3333 root->type.find("typedef ")==-1 // and not a typedef
3334 ) ||
3335 (root->section.isFunction() && // or maybe a function pointer variable
3336 (isFuncPtr=findFunctionPtr(root->type.str(),root->lang))!=-1
3337 ) ||
3338 (root->section.isFunction() && // class variable initialized by constructor
3339 isVarWithConstructor(root)
3340 )
3341 )
3342 ) // documented variable
3343 {
3344 AUTO_TRACE();
3345 addVariable(root,isFuncPtr);
3346 }
3347 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3348 if (!e->section.isEnum())
3349 buildVarList(e.get());
3350}

3352//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3353// Searches the Entry tree for Interface sections (UNO IDL only).
3354// If found they are stored in their service or in the global list.
3355//
3356
3357static void addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(
3358 const Entry *root,
3359 ClassDefMutable *cd,
3360 QCString const& rname)
3361{
3362 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
3363 enum MemberType type = root->section.isExportedInterface() ? MemberType::Interface : MemberType::Service;
3364 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3365 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
3366 {
3367 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
3368 }
3369 auto md = createMemberDef(
3370 fileName, root->startLine, root->startColumn, root->type, rname,
3371 "", "", root->protection, root->virt, root->isStatic, Relationship::Member,
3372 type, ArgumentList(), root->argList, root->metaData);
3373 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
3374 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3375 mmd->setMemberClass(cd);
3376 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3377 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(false);
3378 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3379 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3380 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3381 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3382 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
3383 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3384 mmd->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3385 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
3386 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
3387 mmd->setFileDef(fd);
3388 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3389 QCString const def = root->type + " " + rname;
3390 mmd->setDefinition(def);
3391 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
3392 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3393
3394 AUTO_TRACE("Interface member: fileName='{}' type='{}' name='{}' mtype='{}' prot={} virt={} state={} proto={} def='{}'",
3395 fileName,root->type,rname,type,root->protection,root->virt,root->isStatic,root->proto,def);
3396
3397 // add member to the class cd
3398 cd->insertMember(md.get());
3399 // also add the member as a "base" (to get nicer diagrams)
3400 // "optional" interface/service get Protected which turns into dashed line
3401 BaseInfo base(rname,
3402 root->spec.isOptional() ? Protection::Protected : Protection::Public, Specifier::Normal);
3403 TemplateNameMap templateNames;
3404 findClassRelation(root,cd,cd,&base,templateNames,DocumentedOnly,true) ||
3405 findClassRelation(root,cd,cd,&base,templateNames,Undocumented,true);
3406 // add file to list of used files
3407 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3408
3409 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3410 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md.get());
3411 root->markAsProcessed();
3412 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
3413
3414 // add member to the global list of all members
3415 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(rname);
3416 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3417}
3418
3419static void buildInterfaceAndServiceList(const Entry *root)
3420{
3421 if (root->section.isExportedInterface() || root->section.isIncludedService())
3422 {
3423 AUTO_TRACE("Exported interface/included service: type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}'"
3424 " relates='{}' relatesType='{}' file='{}' line={} bodyLine={} #tArgLists={}"
3425 " mGrpId={} spec={} proto={} docFile='{}'",
3426 root->type, root->parent()->name, root->name, root->args,
3427 root->relates, root->relatesType, root->fileName, root->startLine, root->bodyLine, root->tArgLists.size(),
3428 root->mGrpId, root->spec, root->proto, root->docFile);
3429
3430 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3431
3432 if (!rname.isEmpty())
3433 {
3434 QCString scope = root->parent()->name;
3435 ClassDefMutable *cd = getClassMutable(scope);
3436 assert(cd);
3437 if (cd && ((ClassDef::Interface == cd->compoundType()) ||
3438 (ClassDef::Service == cd->compoundType()) ||
3439 (ClassDef::Singleton == cd->compoundType())))
3440 {
3441 addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(root,cd,rname);
3442 }
3443 else
3444 {
3445 assert(false); // was checked by scanner.l
3446 }
3447 }
3448 else if (rname.isEmpty())
3449 {
3450 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3451 "Illegal member name found.");
3452 }
3453 }
3454 // can only have these in IDL anyway
3455 switch (root->lang)
3456 {
3457 case SrcLangExt::Unknown: // fall through (root node always is Unknown)
3458 case SrcLangExt::IDL:
3459 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildInterfaceAndServiceList(e.get());
3460 break;
3461 default:
3462 return; // nothing to do here
3463 }
3464}
3465
3466
3467//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3468// Searches the Entry tree for Function sections.
3469// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3470
3471static void addMethodToClass(const Entry *root,ClassDefMutable *cd,
3472 const QCString &rtype,const QCString &rname,const QCString &rargs,
3473 bool isFriend,
3474 Protection protection,bool stat,Specifier virt,TypeSpecifier spec,
3475 const QCString &relates
3476 )
3477{
3478 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3479
3480 QCString type = rtype;
3481 QCString args = rargs;
3482
3483 QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3484 name.stripPrefix("::");
3485
3486 MemberType mtype = MemberType::Function;
3487 if (isFriend) mtype=MemberType::Friend;
3488 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Signal) mtype=MemberType::Signal;
3489 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Slot) mtype=MemberType::Slot;
3490 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::DCOP) mtype=MemberType::DCOP;
3491
3492 // strip redundant template specifier for constructors
3493 int i = -1;
3494 int j = -1;
3495 if ((fd==nullptr || fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt::Cpp) &&
3496 !name.startsWith("operator ") && // not operator
3497 (i=name.find('<'))!=-1 && // containing <
3498 (j=name.find('>'))!=-1 && // or >
3499 (j!=i+2 || name.at(i+1)!='=') // but not the C++20 spaceship operator <=>
3500 )
3501 {
3502 name=name.left(i);
3503 }
3504
3505 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3506 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
3507 {
3508 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
3509 }
3510
3511 //printf("root->name='%s; args='%s' root->argList='%s'\n",
3512 // qPrint(root->name),qPrint(args),qPrint(argListToString(root->argList))
3513 // );
3514
3515 // adding class member
3516 Relationship relationship = relates.isEmpty() ? Relationship::Member :
3517 root->relatesType==RelatesType::MemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign :
3518 Relationship::Related ;
3519 auto md = createMemberDef(
3520 fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3521 type,name,args,root->exception,
3522 protection,virt,
3523 stat && root->relatesType!=RelatesType::MemberOf,
3524 relationship,
3525 mtype,!root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList(),
3526 root->argList, root->metaData);
3527 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
3528 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3529 mmd->setMemberClass(cd);
3530 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3531 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3532 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3533 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3534 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3535 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
3536 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
3537 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3538 mmd->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3539 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
3540 mmd->setRequiresClause(root->req);
3541 mmd->setId(root->id);
3542 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
3543 mmd->setFileDef(fd);
3544 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3545 QCString def;
3546 QCString qualScope = cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
3547 SrcLangExt lang = cd->getLanguage();
3548 QCString scopeSeparator=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
3549 if (scopeSeparator!="::")
3550 {
3551 qualScope = substitute(qualScope,"::",scopeSeparator);
3552 }
3553 if (lang==SrcLangExt::PHP)
3554 {
3555 // for PHP we use Class::method and Namespace\method
3556 scopeSeparator="::";
3557 }
3558// QCString optArgs = root->argList.empty() ? args : QCString();
3559 if (!relates.isEmpty() || isFriend || Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
3560 {
3561 if (!type.isEmpty())
3562 {
3563 def=type+" "+name; //+optArgs;
3564 }
3565 else
3566 {
3567 def=name; //+optArgs;
3568 }
3569 }
3570 else
3571 {
3572 if (!type.isEmpty())
3573 {
3574 def=type+" "+qualScope+scopeSeparator+name; //+optArgs;
3575 }
3576 else
3577 {
3578 def=qualScope+scopeSeparator+name; //+optArgs;
3579 }
3580 }
3581 def.stripPrefix("friend ");
3582 mmd->setDefinition(def);
3583 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
3584 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3585
3586 AUTO_TRACE("function member: type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' proto={} def='{}'",
3587 type, qualScope, rname, args, root->proto, def);
3588
3589 // add member to the class cd
3590 cd->insertMember(md.get());
3591 // add file to list of used files
3592 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3593
3594 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3595 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md.get());
3596 root->markAsProcessed();
3597 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
3598
3599 // add member to the global list of all members
3600 //printf("Adding member=%s class=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(cd->name()));
3601 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3602 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3603}

3606
3607static void addGlobalFunction(const Entry *root,const QCString &rname,const QCString &sc)
3608{
3609 QCString scope = sc;
3610
3611 // new global function
3612 QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3613 auto md = createMemberDef(
3614 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3615 root->type,name,root->args,root->exception,
3616 root->protection,root->virt,root->isStatic,Relationship::Member,
3617 MemberType::Function,
3618 !root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList(),
3619 root->argList,root->metaData);
3620 auto mmd = toMemberDefMutable(md.get());
3621 mmd->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3622 mmd->setLanguage(root->lang);
3623 mmd->setId(root->id);
3624 mmd->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3625 mmd->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3626 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3627 mmd->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3628 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3629 mmd->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3630 //md->setBody(root->body);
3631 mmd->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3632 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3633 mmd->setBodyDef(fd);
3634 mmd->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3635 mmd->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3636 mmd->setVhdlSpecifiers(root->vhdlSpec);
3637 mmd->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3638 mmd->setRequiresClause(root->req);
3639 mmd->setExplicitExternal(root->explicitExternal,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3640
3641 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = nullptr;
3642 // see if the function is inside a namespace that was not part of
3643 // the name already (in that case nd should be non-zero already)
3644 if (root->parent()->section.isNamespace())
3645 {
3646 //QCString nscope=removeAnonymousScopes(root->parent()->name);
3647 QCString nscope=root->parent()->name;
3648 if (!nscope.isEmpty())
3649 {
3650 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(nscope);
3651 }
3652 }
3653 else if (root->parent()->section.isGroupDoc() && !scope.isEmpty())
3654 {
3655 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(sc);
3656 }
3657
3658 if (!scope.isEmpty())
3659 {
3660 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(root->lang);
3661 if (sep!="::")
3662 {
3663 scope = substitute(scope,"::",sep);
3664 }
3665 scope+=sep;
3666 }
3667
3668 if (Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES)) scope = "";
3669 QCString def;
3670 //QCString optArgs = root->argList.empty() ? QCString() : root->args;
3671 if (!root->type.isEmpty())
3672 {
3673 def=root->type+" "+scope+name; //+optArgs;
3674 }
3675 else
3676 {
3677 def=scope+name; //+optArgs;
3678 }
3679 AUTO_TRACE("new non-member function type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' proto={} def='{}'",
3680 root->type,scope,rname,root->args,root->proto,def);
3681 mmd->setDefinition(def);
3682 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,mmd);
3683 mmd->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3684
3685 mmd->setRefItems(root->sli);
3686 if (nd && !nd->name().isEmpty() && nd->name().at(0)!='@')
3687 {
3688 // add member to namespace
3689 mmd->setNamespace(nd);
3690 nd->insertMember(md.get());
3691 }
3692 if (fd)
3693 {
3694 // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3695 // inserted it into the namespace)
3696 mmd->setFileDef(fd);
3697 fd->insertMember(md.get());
3698 }
3699
3700 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3701 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md.get());
3702 if (root->relatesType == RelatesType::Simple) // if this is a relatesalso command,
3703 // allow find Member to pick it up
3704 {
3705 root->markAsProcessed(); // Otherwise we have finished with this entry.
3706 }
3707
3708 // add member to the list of file members
3709 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3710 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3711}

3713//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3714
3715static void buildFunctionList(const Entry *root)
3716{
3717 if (root->section.isFunction())
3718 {
3719 AUTO_TRACE("member function: type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' relates='{}' relatesType='{}'"
3720 " file='{}' line={} bodyLine={} #tArgLists={} mGrpId={}"
3721 " spec={} proto={} docFile='{}'",
3722 root->type, root->parent()->name, root->name, root->args, root->relates, root->relatesType,
3723 root->fileName, root->startLine, root->bodyLine, root->tArgLists.size(), root->mGrpId,
3724 root->spec, root->proto, root->docFile);
3725
3726 bool isFriend=root->type.find("friend ")!=-1;
3727 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3728 //printf("rname=%s\n",qPrint(rname));
3729
3730 QCString scope;
3731 int index = computeQualifiedIndex(rname);
3732 if (index!=-1 && root->parent()->section.isGroupDoc() && root->parent()->tagInfo())
3733 // grouped members are stored with full scope
3734 {
3735 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(rname.left(index+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo());
3736 scope=rname.left(index);
3737 rname=rname.mid(index+2);
3738 }
3739 else
3740 {
3741 scope=root->parent()->name; //stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->parent->name);
3742 }
3743 if (!rname.isEmpty() && scope.find('@')==-1)
3744 {
3745 // check if this function's parent is a class
3746 scope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(scope,FALSE);
3747
3748 FileDef *rfd=root->fileDef();
3749
3750 int memIndex=rname.findRev("::");
3751
3752 ClassDefMutable *cd=getClassMutable(scope);
3753 if (cd && scope+"::"==rname.left(scope.length()+2)) // found A::f inside A
3754 {
3755 // strip scope from name
3756 rname=rname.right(rname.length()-root->parent()->name.length()-2);
3757 }
3758
3759 bool isMember=FALSE;
3760 if (memIndex!=-1)
3761 {
3762 int ts=rname.find('<');
3763 int te=rname.find('>');
3764 if (memIndex>0 && (ts==-1 || te==-1))
3765 {
3766 // note: the following code was replaced by inMember=TRUE to deal with a
3767 // function rname='X::foo' of class X inside a namespace also called X...
3768 // bug id 548175
3769 //nd = Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(rname.left(memIndex));
3770 //isMember = nd==nullptr;
3771 //if (nd)
3772 //{
3773 // // strip namespace scope from name
3774 // scope=rname.left(memIndex);
3775 // rname=rname.right(rname.length()-memIndex-2);
3776 //}
3777 isMember = TRUE;
3778 }
3779 else
3780 {
3781 isMember=memIndex<ts || memIndex>te;
3782 }
3783 }
3784
3785 if (!root->parent()->name.isEmpty() && root->parent()->section.isCompound() && cd)
3786 {
3787 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("member '{}' of class '{}'", rname,cd->name());
3788 addMethodToClass(root,cd,root->type,rname,root->args,isFriend,
3789 root->protection,root->isStatic,root->virt,root->spec,root->relates);
3790 }
3791 else if (root->parent()->section.isObjcImpl() && cd)
3792 {
3793 const MemberDef *md = cd->getMemberByName(rname);
3794 if (md)
3795 {
3796 MemberDefMutable *mdm = toMemberDefMutable(const_cast<MemberDef*>(md));
3797 if (mdm)
3798 {
3799 mdm->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3800 mdm->setBodyDef(root->fileDef());
3801 }
3802 }
3803 }
3804 else if (!root->parent()->section.isCompound() && !root->parent()->section.isObjcImpl() &&
3805 !isMember &&
3806 (root->relates.isEmpty() || root->relatesType==RelatesType::Duplicate) &&
3807 !root->type.startsWith("extern ") && !root->type.startsWith("typedef ")
3808 )
3809 // no member => unrelated function
3810 {
3811 /* check the uniqueness of the function name in the file.
3812 * A file could contain a function prototype and a function definition
3813 * or even multiple function prototypes.
3814 */
3815 bool found=FALSE;
3816 MemberDef *md_found=nullptr;
3817 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(rname);
3818 if (mn)
3819 {
3820 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("function '{}' already found",rname);
3821 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
3822 {
3823 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
3824 if (md)
3825 {
3826 const NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
3827 NamespaceDef *rnd = nullptr;
3828 //printf("root namespace=%s\n",qPrint(rootNav->parent()->name()));
3829 QCString fullScope = scope;
3830 QCString parentScope = root->parent()->name;
3831 if (!parentScope.isEmpty() && !leftScopeMatch(parentScope,scope))
3832 {
3833 if (!scope.isEmpty()) fullScope.prepend("::");
3834 fullScope.prepend(parentScope);
3835 }
3836 //printf("fullScope=%s\n",qPrint(fullScope));
3837 rnd = getResolvedNamespace(fullScope);
3838 const FileDef *mfd = md->getFileDef();
3839 QCString nsName,rnsName;
3840 if (mnd) nsName = mnd->name();
3841 if (rnd) rnsName = rnd->name();
3842 //printf("matching arguments for %s%s %s%s\n",
3843 // qPrint(md->name()),md->argsString(),qPrint(rname),qPrint(argListToString(root->argList)));
3844 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md->argumentList();
3845 const ArgumentList &mdTempl = md->templateArguments();
3846
3847 // in case of template functions, we need to check if the
3848 // functions have the same number of template parameters
3849 bool sameNumTemplateArgs = TRUE;
3850 bool matchingReturnTypes = TRUE;
3851 bool sameRequiresClause = TRUE;
3852 if (!mdTempl.empty() && !root->tArgLists.empty())
3853 {
3854 if (mdTempl.size()!=root->tArgLists.back().size())
3855 {
3856 sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3857 }
3858 if (md->typeString()!=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->type))
3859 {
3860 matchingReturnTypes = FALSE;
3861 }
3862 if (md->requiresClause()!=root->req)
3863 {
3864 sameRequiresClause = FALSE;
3865 }
3866 }
3867 else if (!mdTempl.empty() || !root->tArgLists.empty())
3868 { // if one has template parameters and the other doesn't then that also counts as a
3869 // difference
3870 sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3871 }
3872
3873 bool staticsInDifferentFiles =
3874 root->isStatic && md->isStatic() && root->fileName!=md->getDefFileName();
3875
3876 if (
3877 matchArguments2(md->getOuterScope(),mfd,&mdAl,
3878 rnd ? rnd : Doxygen::globalScope,rfd,&root->argList,
3879 FALSE,root->lang) &&
3880 sameNumTemplateArgs &&
3881 matchingReturnTypes &&
3882 sameRequiresClause &&
3883 !staticsInDifferentFiles
3884 )
3885 {
3886 GroupDef *gd=nullptr;
3887 if (!root->groups.empty() && !root->groups.front().groupname.isEmpty())
3888 {
3889 gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(root->groups.front().groupname);
3890 }
3891 //printf("match!\n");
3892 //printf("mnd=%p rnd=%p nsName=%s rnsName=%s\n",mnd,rnd,qPrint(nsName),qPrint(rnsName));
3893 // see if we need to create a new member
3894 found=(mnd && rnd && nsName==rnsName) || // members are in the same namespace
3895 ((mnd==nullptr && rnd==nullptr && mfd!=nullptr && // no external reference and
3896 mfd->absFilePath()==root->fileName // prototype in the same file
3897 )
3898 );
3899 // otherwise, allow a duplicate global member with the same argument list
3900 if (!found && gd && gd==md->getGroupDef() && nsName==rnsName)
3901 {
3902 // member is already in the group, so we don't want to add it again.
3903 found=TRUE;
3904 }
3905
3906 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("combining function with prototype found={} in namespace '{}'",found,nsName);
3907
3908 if (found)
3909 {
3910 // merge argument lists
3911 ArgumentList mergedArgList = root->argList;
3912 mergeArguments(const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdAl),mergedArgList,!root->doc.isEmpty());
3913 // merge documentation
3914 if (md->documentation().isEmpty() && !root->doc.isEmpty())
3915 {
3916 if (root->proto)
3917 {
3918 md->moveDeclArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(root->lang,root->args));
3919 }
3920 else
3921 {
3922 md->moveArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(root->lang,root->args));
3923 }
3924 }
3925
3926 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3927 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3928 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3929 if (md->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && root->bodyLine!=-1)
3930 {
3931 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3932 md->setBodyDef(rfd);
3933 }
3934
3935 if (md->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !root->brief.isEmpty())
3936 {
3937 md->setArgsString(root->args);
3938 }
3939 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3940
3941 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3942
3943 applyMemberOverrideOptions(root,md);
3944 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3945
3946 // merge ingroup specifiers
3947 if (md->getGroupDef()==nullptr && !root->groups.empty())
3948 {
3949 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3950 }
3951 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=nullptr && root->groups.empty())
3952 {
3953 //printf("existing member is grouped, new member not\n");
3954 }
3955 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=nullptr && !root->groups.empty())
3956 {
3957 //printf("both members are grouped\n");
3958 }
3959 ModuleManager::instance().addMemberToModule(root,md);
3960
3961 // if md is a declaration and root is the corresponding
3962 // definition, then turn md into a definition.
3963 if (md->isPrototype() && !root->proto)
3964 {
3965 md->setDeclFile(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine(),md->getDefColumn());
3966 md->setPrototype(FALSE,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3967 }
3968 // if md is already the definition, then add the declaration info
3969 else if (!md->isPrototype() && root->proto)
3970 {
3971 md->setDeclFile(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3972 }
3973 }
3974 }
3975 }
3976 if (found)
3977 {
3978 md_found = md;
3979 break;
3980 }
3981 }
3982 }
3983 if (!found) /* global function is unique with respect to the file */
3984 {
3985 addGlobalFunction(root,rname,scope);
3986 }
3987 else
3988 {
3989 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3990 if (fd)
3991 {
3992 // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3993 // inserted it into the namespace)
3994 fd->insertMember(md_found);
3995 }
3996 }
3997
3998 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("unrelated function type='{}' name='{}' args='{}'",root->type,rname,root->args);
3999 }
4000 else
4001 {
4002 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("function '{}' is not processed",rname);
4003 }
4004 }
4005 else if (rname.isEmpty())
4006 {
4007 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
4008 "Illegal member name found."
4009 );
4010 }
4011 }
4012 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildFunctionList(e.get());
4013}

4016
4017static void findFriends()
4018{
4019 AUTO_TRACE();
4020 for (const auto &fn : *Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap) // for each global function name
4021 {
4022 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->find(fn->memberName());
4023 if (mn)
4024 { // there are members with the same name
4025 // for each function with that name
4026 for (const auto &ifmd : *fn)
4027 {
4028 MemberDefMutable *fmd = toMemberDefMutable(ifmd.get());
4029 // for each member with that name
4030 for (const auto &immd : *mn)
4031 {
4032 MemberDefMutable *mmd = toMemberDefMutable(immd.get());
4033 //printf("Checking for matching arguments
4034 // mmd->isRelated()=%d mmd->isFriend()=%d mmd->isFunction()=%d\n",
4035 // mmd->isRelated(),mmd->isFriend(),mmd->isFunction());
4036 if (fmd && mmd &&
4037 (mmd->isFriend() || (mmd->isRelated() && mmd->isFunction())) &&
4038 matchArguments2(mmd->getOuterScope(), mmd->getFileDef(), &mmd->argumentList(),
4039 fmd->getOuterScope(), fmd->getFileDef(), &fmd->argumentList(),
4040 TRUE,mmd->getLanguage()
4041 )
4042
4043 ) // if the member is related and the arguments match then the
4044 // function is actually a friend.
4045 {
4046 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Merging related global and member '{}' isFriend={} isRelated={} isFunction={}",
4047 mmd->name(),mmd->isFriend(),mmd->isRelated(),mmd->isFunction());
4048 const ArgumentList &mmdAl = mmd->argumentList();
4049 const ArgumentList &fmdAl = fmd->argumentList();
4050 mergeArguments(const_cast<ArgumentList&>(fmdAl),const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mmdAl));
4051
4052 // reset argument lists to add missing default parameters
4053 QCString mmdAlStr = argListToString(mmdAl);
4054 QCString fmdAlStr = argListToString(fmdAl);
4055 mmd->setArgsString(mmdAlStr);
4056 fmd->setArgsString(fmdAlStr);
4057 mmd->moveDeclArgumentList(std::make_unique<ArgumentList>(mmdAl));
4058 fmd->moveDeclArgumentList(std::make_unique<ArgumentList>(fmdAl));
4059 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("friend args='{}' member args='{}'",argListToString(fmd->argumentList()),argListToString(mmd->argumentList()));
4060
4061 if (!fmd->documentation().isEmpty())
4062 {
4063 mmd->setDocumentation(fmd->documentation(),fmd->docFile(),fmd->docLine());
4064 }
4065 else if (!mmd->documentation().isEmpty())
4066 {
4067 fmd->setDocumentation(mmd->documentation(),mmd->docFile(),mmd->docLine());
4068 }
4069 if (mmd->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !fmd->briefDescription().isEmpty())
4070 {
4071 mmd->setBriefDescription(fmd->briefDescription(),fmd->briefFile(),fmd->briefLine());
4072 }
4073 else if (!mmd->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !fmd->briefDescription().isEmpty())
4074 {
4075 fmd->setBriefDescription(mmd->briefDescription(),mmd->briefFile(),mmd->briefLine());
4076 }
4077 if (!fmd->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
4078 {
4079 mmd->setInbodyDocumentation(fmd->inbodyDocumentation(),fmd->inbodyFile(),fmd->inbodyLine());
4080 }
4081 else if (!mmd->inbodyDocumentation().isEmpty())
4082 {
4083 fmd->setInbodyDocumentation(mmd->inbodyDocumentation(),mmd->inbodyFile(),mmd->inbodyLine());
4084 }
4085 //printf("body mmd %d fmd %d\n",mmd->getStartBodyLine(),fmd->getStartBodyLine());
4086 if (mmd->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && fmd->getStartBodyLine()!=-1)
4087 {
4088 mmd->setBodySegment(fmd->getDefLine(),fmd->getStartBodyLine(),fmd->getEndBodyLine());
4089 mmd->setBodyDef(fmd->getBodyDef());
4090 //mmd->setBodyMember(fmd);
4091 }
4092 else if (mmd->getStartBodyLine()!=-1 && fmd->getStartBodyLine()==-1)
4093 {
4094 fmd->setBodySegment(mmd->getDefLine(),mmd->getStartBodyLine(),mmd->getEndBodyLine());
4095 fmd->setBodyDef(mmd->getBodyDef());
4096 //fmd->setBodyMember(mmd);
4097 }
4098 mmd->setDocsForDefinition(fmd->isDocsForDefinition());
4099
4100 mergeMemberOverrideOptions(mmd,fmd);
4101
4102 mmd->addQualifiers(fmd->getQualifiers());
4103 fmd->addQualifiers(mmd->getQualifiers());
4104
4105 }
4106 }
4107 }

12716 auto memberNameComp = [](const MemberNameLinkedMap::Ptr &n1,const MemberNameLinkedMap::Ptr &n2)
12717 {
12718 return qstricmp_sort(n1->memberName().data()+getPrefixIndex(n1->memberName()),
12719 n2->memberName().data()+getPrefixIndex(n2->memberName())
12720 )<0;
12721 };
12722
12723 auto classComp = [](const ClassLinkedMap::Ptr &c1,const ClassLinkedMap::Ptr &c2)
12724 {
12725 if (Config_getBool(SORT_BY_SCOPE_NAME))
12726 {
12727 return qstricmp_sort(c1->name(), c2->name())<0;
12728 }
12729 else
12730 {
12731 int i = qstricmp_sort(c1->className(), c2->className());
12732 return i==0 ? qstricmp_sort(c1->name(), c2->name())<0 : i<0;
12733 }
12734 };
12735
12736 auto namespaceComp = [](const NamespaceLinkedMap::Ptr &n1,const NamespaceLinkedMap::Ptr &n2)
12737 {
12738 return qstricmp_sort(n1->name(),n2->name())<0;
12739 };
12740
12741 auto conceptComp = [](const ConceptLinkedMap::Ptr &c1,const ConceptLinkedMap::Ptr &c2)
12742 {
12743 return qstricmp_sort(c1->name(),c2->name())<0;
12744 };
12745
12746 g_s.begin("Sorting lists...\n");
12747 std::stable_sort(Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->begin(),
12748 Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->end(),
12749 memberNameComp);
12750 std::stable_sort(Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->begin(),
12751 Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->end(),
12752 memberNameComp);
12753 std::stable_sort(Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->begin(),
12754 Doxygen::hiddenClassLinkedMap->end(),
12755 classComp);
12756 std::stable_sort(Doxygen::classLinkedMap->begin(),
12757 Doxygen::classLinkedMap->end(),
12758 classComp);
12759 std::stable_sort(Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap->begin(),
12760 Doxygen::conceptLinkedMap->end(),
12761 conceptComp);
12762 std::stable_sort(Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->begin(),
12763 Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->end(),
12764 namespaceComp);
12765 g_s.end();

◆ processTagLessClasses()

static void processTagLessClasses ( const ClassDef * rootCd,
const ClassDef * cd,
ClassDefMutable * tagParentCd,
const QCString & prefix,
int count )
static

Look through the members of class cd and its public members.

If there is a member m of a tag less struct/union, then we create a duplicate of the struct/union with the name of the member to identify it. So if cd has name S, then the tag less struct/union will get name S.m Since tag less structs can be nested we need to call this function recursively. Later on we need to patch the member types so we keep track of the hierarchy of classes we create.
